description: Sorry for the potato quality. I only had my phone but I had to photograph it because it freaked me out and I needed to know what it was. They fittingly call these things assassin bugs. Apparently it’s an invasive species in Japan and didn’t reach Kanto until the 1990s. Well I can officially confirm they’re still here. This seems to be its final molting stage before its exoskeleton hardens. Sometimes they bite people so don’t get too close. Google a bunch of photos of these—it’s a great way to get goosebumps. *shivers*

description:
We’ve seen this animal at least 3 times over 2 years but have no idea what it could be. Its tail is as long as the rest of its body, its head is rather cone shaped and has a white stripe going from its forehead down to its nose. Its fur seemed rather short and its tail wasn’t particularly fluffy.

We live very close to a zoo and are wondering if it could have escaped and grown accustomed to the city. It looks a lot like a coati, but with a white stripe on its head.

Sorry about the image quality, we’ve only ever seen it at night.
